revision.text:
{{italic title}} [[File:Archivos do Museu Nacional do Rio de Janeiro BHL4958709.jpg|thumb|A page from the 1885 edition of the journal]] '''''Arquivos do Museu Nacional''''' (previously '''''Archivos do Museu Nacional'''''; [[International Standard Serial Number|ISSN]]: 0365-4508) is the oldest [[scientific journal]] of Brazil.<ref name="arquivo-vol63">{{Cite document|title=Arquivos do Museu Nacional Vol. 62 N. 3|year=2004|url=http://www.museunacional.ufrj.br/publicacoes/wp-content/arquivos/Arqs%2062%20n%203%20Completo.pdf|archiveurl=https://ia601507.us.archive.org/9/items/arquivos-mn-vol62-n3/Arqs%2062%20n%203%20Completo.pdf|archivedate=2018-09-03}}</ref> Its first issue was published in 1876, founded by [[Ladislau de Souza Mello Netto]].<ref name="arquivo-vol63"/><ref name="GlickPuig-Samper2012">{{cite book|author1=T.F Glick|author2=Miguel Angel Puig-Samper|author3=R. Ruiz|title=The Reception of Darwinism in the Iberian World: Spain, Spanish America and Brazil|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dRsyBwAAQBAJ&pg=PA70|date=6 December 2012|publisher=Springer Science & Business Media|isbn=978-94-010-0602-6|page=70}}</ref> The journal is edited and published quarterly (March, June, September and December) by the [[National Museum of Brazil]] and the [[Federal University of Rio de Janeiro]].<ref name="arquivo-vol63"/> The journal areas cover anthropology, archaeology, botany, geology, paleontology and zoology.<ref name="arquivo-vol63"/>
