'''Eshkaft-e Siahoo''' ({{lang-fa|اشکفت سیاهو}}), which means "black cave" in the dialect of the people of the region, is a 10,000-year-old [[neolithic]] stone dwelling near [[Rahmat Mountain]] in the [[Marvdasht Plain]] in the [[Fars province]], [[Iran]]. The cave was discovered in June 2006. 

