{{Infobox journal | title = Tidsskrift for Rettsvitenskap | abbreviation = Tidsskr. Rettsvitensk. | cover = | editor = [[Viggo Hagstrøm]] | language = Scandinavian (Danish, Norwegian, Swedish) | formernames = Tidsskrift for Retsvidenskab ''(1888–1932),'' Tidsskrift for Rettsvidenskap ''(1932–1939)'' | discipline = Law | publisher = [[Universitetsforlaget]] | country = Norway | frequency = 5/year | history = 1888-present | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.universitetsforlaget.no/tidsskrift/vaare/juss/llvn_tfs | link2 = http://www.idunn.no/ts/tfr | link2-name = Online access | ISSN = 0040-7143 | eISSN = 1504-3096 }} '''''Tidsskrift for Rettsvitenskap''''' (English: "Journal of Jurisprudence") is a Norwegian [[law journal]]. It was established in 1888 by [[Francis Hagerup]] to "form a link between legal research in the [[Nordic countries]]" and is currently published by [[Universitetsforlaget]]. The journal is one of Scandinavia's preeminent academic journals in the field of law.<ref>Internasjonal politikk, Volum 65, 2007</ref> It is ranked as a Level 2 journal, the highest level in the official Norwegian ranking (the [[Norwegian Scientific Index]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dbh.nsd.uib.no/kanaler/kanalDetalj.do?produktid=340946 |title=Publiseringskanaler |publisher=Dbh.nsd.uib.no |date= |accessdate=2012-01-28}}</ref> Articles are published in the three Scandinavian languages: Danish, Norwegian, and Swedish.
The original spelling of the journal name was ''Tidsskrift for Retsvidenskab'', which was changed to ''Tidsskrift for Rettsvidenskap'' in 1932 and to ''Tidsskrift for Rettsvitenskap'' in 1940, i.e. from a Danish spelling to a modern Norwegian spelling.
== Editors-in-chief == [[File:Georg Francis Hagerup.jpg|thumb|The journal's founder and editor for 33 years, two times Prime Minister [[Francis Hagerup]]]] The following persons have been editors-in-chief of the journal, most of them worked at the [[Faculty of Law, University of Oslo]]: * [[Francis Hagerup]] 1888–1921<ref>[http://snl.no/Francis_Hagerup Francis Hagerup], ''[[Store Norske Leksikon]]''</ref> * [[Fredrik Stang]] 1922–1936<ref>[http://snl.no/Fredrik_Stang Fredrik Stang], ''[[Store Norske Leksikon]]''</ref> * [[Erik Solem]] 1939–1949<ref>[http://snl.no/Erik_Solem Erik Solem], ''[[Store Norske Leksikon]]''</ref> * [[Carl Jacob Arnholm]] ?–1962<ref name="ifp-hist">{{no icon}} http://www.jus.uio.no/ifp/om/historie/ifp50ar.pdf</ref> * [[Knut Selmer]] 1963–1964<ref name="ifp-hist"/> * [[Carsten Smith]] 1963–1973<ref name="ifp-hist"/> * [[Birger Stuevold Lassen]] 1974–1999<ref name="ifp-hist"/> * [[Viggo Hagstrøm]] 1999–2013
